Package uk.ac.ed.inf.aqmaps.webserver

Class WebServerFileFetcher

java.lang.Object
uk.ac.ed.inf.aqmaps.webserver.WebServerFileFetcher
public class WebServerFileFetcher
extends java.lang.Object
Instances of this class are directly responsible for retrieving files from the web server that is used to store data relevant to this application.

    • WebServerFileFetcher

      public WebServerFileFetcher​(int port)
      The constructor of the WebServerFileFetcher class. All information it needs to retrieve files is static, except the port, which depends on the command line arguments used when running this application.
      Parameters:
      port - the port the web server runs on.

  • Method Details

    • getBuildingsGeojsonFromServer

      public java.lang.String getBuildingsGeojsonFromServer()
      This method can be used to retrieve the file contents corresponding to the no fly zones used in this scenario from the web server.
      Returns:
      the no-fly-zones.geojson file contents as a String

    • getSensorsGeojsonFromServer

      public java.lang.String getSensorsGeojsonFromServer​(int day, int month, int year)
      This method can be used to retrieve the file contents corresponding to the sensors to be read on a given date from the web server.
      Parameters:
      day - the day of month corresponding to this program execution
      month - the month corresponding to this program execution
      year - the year corresponding to this program execution
      Returns:
      the String contents of the air-quality-data.json file for the given date

    • getW3wJsonFromServer

      public java.lang.String getW3wJsonFromServer​(java.lang.String first, java.lang.String second, java.lang.String third)
      This method can be used to retrieve the file contents corresponding to the W3W location with the given identifier.
      Parameters:
      first - the first word of the W3W identifier
      second - the second word of the W3W identifier
      third - the third word of the W3W identifier
      Returns:
      the String contents of the details.json file for the given location
